reviews.headline: Not bad! But not my favorite
reviews.comments: I had high hopes for the Exuviance Pro-Plump Hydrating Cream, and while it did deliver some hydration and a slight plumping effect, it didn't quite wow me. The texture is nice and lightweight, and it absorbed quickly without feeling greasy, which I appreciated. However, I didn't notice a dramatic improvement in fine lines or firmness over time. It's not a bad product — it just didn't stand out compared to others I've tried at a similar price point. Overall, it's okay, but I wouldn't call it a must-have.

reviews.headline: Super hydrating
reviews.comments:
I've been using the Exuviance Pro-Plump Hydrating Cream and it's a total game changer for my skincare routine. The texture is lightweight yet deeply hydrating, and it absorbs quickly without feeling greasy. After just a few uses, I noticed my skin felt more plump, smooth, and looked visibly more refreshed.

The combination of Hyaluronic Acid and pro-peptide complex gives a real boost of moisture, especially for dry or aging skin. It's been great for smoothing out fine lines and giving my face a more firm, youthful appearance. I love that it leaves a dewy finish without clogging my pores.

If you're looking for something that delivers on hydration and helps fight early signs of aging, this is a must-try. Definitely a staple in my skincare lineup now!

reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Love the scent of this product and its packaging! The ingredients were nice and effective. Texture was smooth and went on nicely. I would recommend this to friends.

reviews.headline: Great for dry skin
reviews.comments: I have been using this for about a month now consecutively. At first I was very hesitant about the quality of this since the lid feels very thin and not of great quality despite it being in decent packaging and in a glass container. This moisturizer is thin and really easy to spread yet super hydrating that does provide the "plump" feeling it promises. After a few days I noticed as if there was separation in the jar between the oil and rest of the product and i'm not sure if that's normal but it's very subtle and doesn't make a different in what i've noticed when I apply anyway. I was considered it would be maybe too "oily" but I have naturally dry skin so it's never been a. concern of mine to break out or have a "greasy" look so if that's a concern for you then this may not be the product. Since my skin is constantly needing to be hydrated this product is perfect to lock in moisture  and I can feel suppleness on my skin for hours later or the next morning after a night routine.

reviews.headline: Hydration
reviews.comments: I definitely felt like this gave hydration support to my face. The smell was very pleasant and it was not greasy at all! I will definitely be incorporating into my skincare routine. I did receive this product complimentary in exchange for my honest review.

reviews.headline: Plump skin for days
reviews.comments:
I was gifted this product in exchange for a review. The soft blue color gives it a refreshing aesthetic, and the texture is buttery smooth. From the first application, my skin felt instantly quenched. It delivers a deep, cushiony moisture that makes my face feel supple and comforted without feeling greasy.  

I love how plump and glowy my skin looks after use, like it just had a full night of sleep and a glass of water. The hydration lasts all day, and over time.

faceoff_positive.comments:
This product comes in a glass container, and as someone who actively tries to avoid plastic whenever possible, I was instantly impressed.

But let's talk about why this product truly felt like it was made for me. I struggle with dry skin, especially in the winter. Living in a humid area helps in the summer, but once the cold months hit, it's a battle.

At first, I was skeptical. The product is marketed as lightweight, but when I applied it to the back of my hand for reference, it felt thick—like, really thick. Even as I rubbed it in, I kept thinking, This is not lightweight at all. But then, I put it on my face… and suddenly, it felt weightless. My brain could not process it. I could still feel the rich, moisturizing layer when I touched my skin, but without touching it? I felt nothing. It's like skincare sorcery 🤣

Now, let's talk fragrance. I am not a fragrance girlie—especially when it comes to facial products. I believe they should be fragrance-free, period. That being said, this one has a subtle, clean scent that doesn't scream artificial or overpowering. It's not floral, fruity, or headache-inducing—it's just fresh, reminds me of a spa. Looking at the ingredients, I saw "parfum/fragrance" listed toward the end, which I appreciate. However, in a perfect world, it would have zero fragrance, and that's the only reason I can't call it my holy grail.

Would I recommend it? Absolutely, ITS SO HYDRATING, and I can't even feel it on my face. Will I be replacing my current go-to? No— but that's ONLY because of the fragrance.

If fragrance doesn't bother you, this is it. It's hydrating, luxurious, and truly locks in moisture. I even considered giving away my other moisturizers because of how good this felt on my skin. But for me, my top pick is still a fragrance-free option—though I will gladly finish this entire jar because, let's be real, it's an amazing product 😍!!!!
faceoff_positive.headline: Thick, yet lightweight 👀😍

faceoff_negative.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This comes in this beautiful matte glass container that is really small for its price and possibly won't last you very long if using it daily or nightly. The consistency of this moisturizer is actually more like a gel type of cream. It's not the lotion cream I would have expected. It has hyaluronic acid and peptides to help moisturize and smooth out those fine lines by plumping your skin. This is what really had peeked my interested about the product itself. When I applied it at night after my shower I noticed that the gel cream is actually pretty lightweight and applied smoothly but it didn't really absorb into my dry sensitive skin as well as I had thought it would once applying it. This also had a light fragrance to it, so I wish I had known this ahead of time as for my skin is sensitive, and it seemed to irritate it a bit. The gel cream itself also left my skin tingling but I figured this could be from the plumping agent but then again maybe I'm just too sensitive for this product. I used it a few times and each time this happened. I sadly wanted to love the product but with my sensitive skin I just can't. Hopefully it works better for someone else. Overall I recommend for anyone who does not have sensitive skin as I do. I received this product for free in exchange for my honest review.
faceoff_negative.headline: Not for my sensitive skin
